{"TopicId":126592,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Kerdinand\u00B4s Military Craft","CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-29T16:49:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-29T16:49:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022c8XinFR.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/c8XinFR.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:750px;height:187px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nNow that the new forum has arrived I think it is time to make my own showcase thread, a collection of my craft. Here you will find mostly military stuff. I build armed vehicles with BD armory, for land, water, air and space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMy naming scheme:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe numbering goes like the following:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[Medium][Craft Type]-[Craft number][Craft version] [Craft name]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nf.e.: DS-1C Lupus\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are four mediums:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nA: Space\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nB: Air\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nC: Ground\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nD: Water \u0026amp; Subwater\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EI will add a detailed list of the craft types here later.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe craft depends on the crafts produced from the same type earlier, if e.g. four interceptors have already been built, the fifth will be called BI-5A.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe verions depends on the version. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe craft name is arbitrarly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMy Action Group System\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will use the same AG system on all of my craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEngines\u003C/strong\u003E are listed from \u003Cstrong\u003E1 up\u003C/strong\u003E. So 1 is primary engine, 2 is secondary engine (or mode switch for primary engine) and so on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECargo Bays\u003C/strong\u003E will always be bound to the first AG after the engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth \u003Cstrong\u003ESolar panels\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003ERadiator panels\u003C/strong\u003E are bound to the first AG after cargo bays. (On the same key!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E5\u003C/strong\u003E will drop \u003Cstrong\u003Eprobes\u003C/strong\u003E, if probes exist\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E6\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003E7\u003C/strong\u003E activate special BD armory functions, like Radar or IR\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E8\u003C/strong\u003E will drop \u003Cstrong\u003Ecountermeasures\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E9\u003C/strong\u003E will cycle through the BDA weapons\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E0\u003C/strong\u003E will fire the selected BDA weapon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EAbort \u003C/strong\u003Ewill activate special things\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EMy Craft:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nHere are my craft, in no particular order. Under each craft picture, there will be a link redirecting you to to the release post (Where you can find detailed information)\u00A0and a download link.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Io3NdTs.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Io3NdTs.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/i1bziajtkiughoc/DS-1c%20Lupus.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PiFH1ho.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/PiFH1ho.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:101px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/126592-kerdinand%C2%B4s-military-craft/#comment-2300365\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uGRuOeS.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uGRuOeS.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:101px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022WUlojU1.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/WUlojU1.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/37ebbgnn5sffs5j/AD-1A%20Sword.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PiFH1ho.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/PiFH1ho.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:101px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/126592-kerdinand%C2%B4s-military-craft/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=2300887\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uGRuOeS.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uGRuOeS.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:101px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-11-30T13:24:25Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2015 01:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Kerdinand\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-29T17:06:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here is the first craft:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Io3NdTs.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Io3NdTs.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe Lupus is a small strike submarine designed to perform quick attacks, but not long-term\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmissions. It is equipped with 3 Hellfire torpedoes for heavier and a 30mm chaingun for lighter\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntargets. It can reach up to 40 m/s and, thanks to TWR \u0026gt;1 with Afterburners, it can also escape\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe water and fly (a bit)! Using its two parachutes and some engines assistance it can also\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsubmerge again savely. Have fun! I suggest Hyperedit for getting it into the water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022af8nyHX.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/af8nyHX.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mtePdod.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mtePdod.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022huFXfLR.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/huFXfLR.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/i1bziajtkiughoc/DS-1c%20Lupus.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uXWmP3q.png?1\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uXWmP3q.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:600px;height:102px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I\u00B4m confident with the post formatting so far. Any feedback on the formatting (and the craft!) would be appreciated!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-11-30T13:16:08Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2015 01:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Kerdinand\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFixed DL link.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-30T13:21:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/WUlojU1.png?1\u0022 alt=\u0022WUlojU1.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe Sword is also a rather small craft (a destroyer to be exact) but unlike the Lupus it was\u003Cbr\u003E\ndesigned for long-range missions where it can use all of its 8000m/s of Delta-v. Once arrived,\u003Cbr\u003E\nthe Sword can do the battle with its 2 20mm Vulcans against heavier and its 8 .50cal turrets\u003Cbr\u003E\nagainst lighter targets. Latter are mounted on 4 small outtriggers and can inflict damage in an\u003Cbr\u003E\nalmost full sphere. The only drawback of the Sword is its low acceleration that makes it\u003Cbr\u003E\nvulnerable in close-in combat. But as long as you keep distance, you should be fine!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JO4Z245.png?1\u0022 alt=\u0022JO4Z245.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/nPGYrxW.png?1\u0022 alt=\u0022nPGYrxW.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/E1IyY5e.png?1\u0022 alt=\u0022E1IyY5e.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/37ebbgnn5sffs5j/AD-1A%20Sword.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uXWmP3q.png?1\u0022 style=\u0022width:600px;height:102px;\u0022 alt=\u0022uXWmP3q.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rigel Agar","CreatedById":156697,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-21T15:25:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi Kerdinand, nice military crafts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}